SPECTRA
=======
This project is a derivative research work and builds upon prior open-source
projects. It is distributed under the Yale Non-Commercial License (see LICENSE).

Upstream / attributed works:

1. ImmunoStruct  (Krishnaswamy Lab, Yale University)
   https://github.com/KrishnaswamyLab/ImmunoStruct
   Provides the multimodal (sequence + structure + biochemical) modeling
   foundation and the EGNN / VAE components on which SPECTRA is based.
   Givechian et al., Nature Machine Intelligence (2025).

2. STAG-LLM  (Kavraki Lab, Rice University)
   https://github.com/KavrakiLab/STAG_public
   Inspiration for the pseudo-heterogeneous graph transformer (per-edge-type
   message passing over the TCR-pMHC interface) and ESM+structure fusion.
   Slone et al., Computational and Structural Biotechnology Journal (2025).

3. ESM-2  (Meta AI / Facebook Research)
   https://github.com/facebookresearch/esm
   Pretrained protein language model used as the sequence backbone.

Original contributions in SPECTRA (see ARCHITECTURE.md):
  - ESM-2 + chain-specific LoRA post-training for TCR/pMHC
  - Multimodal gated cross-attention fusion of language, structure, and
    Rosetta interface energetics
  - Two-stage Rosetta multi-task pretraining
  - The A-H architecture ablation matrix and multi-seed ensembling
